<Project Sdk="Microsoft.NET.Sdk.Razor">

  <PropertyGroup>
    <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>
    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>
    <ImplicitUsings>enable</ImplicitUsings>
    <Nullable>enable</Nullable>
    <!-- Allow the deliberate Microsoft.Extensions.AI.Abstractions downgrade below (see note on package references). -->
    <NoWarn>$(NoWarn);NU1605</NoWarn>

    <!-- dotnet tool settings -->
    <PackAsTool>true</PackAsTool>
    <ToolCommandName>mandocode</ToolCommandName>
    <PackageId>MandoCode</PackageId>

    <!-- NuGet metadata -->
    <Version>0.9.8</Version>
    <Authors>Armando Fernandez (DevMando)</Authors>
    <Description>Your AI coding assistant — run locally or in the cloud with Ollama. No API keys required. Just you and your code.</Description>
    <PackageProjectUrl>https://github.com/DevMando/MandoCode</PackageProjectUrl>
    <RepositoryUrl>https://github.com/DevMando/MandoCode</RepositoryUrl>
    <PackageLicenseExpression>MIT</PackageLicenseExpression>
    <PackageTags>ai;cli;coding-assistant;ollama;semantic-kernel;local-llm</PackageTags>
    <PackageReadmeFile>README.md</PackageReadmeFile>
    <PackageIcon>MC.png</PackageIcon>
    <ApplicationIcon>MC.ico</ApplicationIcon>
    <PackageReleaseNotes>
v0.9.8 — MCP support, agentic robustness, and live shell streaming

Added:
- MCP (Model Context Protocol) support — connect to any MCP server (stdio or remote HTTP/SSE), tools auto-registered alongside built-in plugins. Interactive `/mcp add` wizard, per-tool first-use approval, `/mcp`, `/mcp tools`, `/mcp remove`, `/mcp-reload`.
- Skills — model can auto-invoke user-defined skills based on name/description, or be force-loaded manually.
- propose_plan tool — models self-classify multi-step requests via a Semantic Kernel function instead of a separate planning round-trip; ~300 lines of fragile text-parsing removed.
- Per-turn circuit breakers, auto-continuation, and synthetic-summary recovery on context-window overflow — long agentic loops no longer silently hang or crash.
- Streaming execute_command — shell tool now streams stdout/stderr line-by-line; the spinner shows live `$ &lt;cmd&gt; → &lt;latest line&gt;` activity.
- Idle-based shell timeout — replaces the old 30s wall-clock kill with a 30s idle timeout (kills only after 30s of no output) plus a 10-minute hard ceiling. Long legitimate builds now run to completion as long as they're emitting output.
- Configurable per-request timeout (`requestTimeoutMinutes`, default 15), tool-result char budget (`toolResultCharBudget`, default 100k), and markdown render timeout (`markdownRenderTimeoutSeconds`, default 60).
- Shell-aware system prompt — detects cmd.exe vs bash and stops the model from emitting `head`/`grep`/`cat` on Windows.

UI:
- Spinner shows elapsed time and rotates its random message every 15s during long waits.
- Live activity row above the spinner (used by streamed shell output, plan steps, MCP tools); persists in scrollback after the spinner stops if it was ever updated.
- Inline auto-continuation and overflow-recovery markers so automatic restarts are visible instead of silent.
- New plan approval UI (Execute / Reject / Cancel) replaces the old "Analyzing..." spinner phase.

Changed:
- Default per-request timeout raised from 5 min to 15 min.
- AIService constructor signature gained PlanHandoff and SpinnerService; FileSystemPlugin constructor gained an optional SpinnerService.
    </PackageReleaseNotes>
  </PropertyGroup>

  <ItemGroup>
    <PackageReference Include="HtmlAgilityPack" Version="1.11.72" />
    <PackageReference Include="Markdig" Version="1.0.0" />
    <PackageReference Include="Microsoft.Extensions.FileSystemGlobbing" Version="10.0.3" />
    <PackageReference Include="Microsoft.SemanticKernel" Version="1.72.0" />
    <PackageReference Include="Microsoft.SemanticKernel.Connectors.Ollama" Version="1.72.0-alpha" />
    <!-- ModelContextProtocol 1.2.0 was compiled against Microsoft.Extensions.AI.Abstractions 10.4.0
         (uses FunctionApprovalRequestContent). That type was removed in 10.4.1 (renamed to
         ToolApprovalRequestContent), so the default NuGet resolution to 10.4.1+ crashes at runtime
         with TypeLoadException. Pin to 10.4.0 until MCP ships a fix. -->
    <PackageReference Include="Microsoft.Extensions.AI.Abstractions" Version="10.4.0" />
    <PackageReference Include="Microsoft.Extensions.AI" Version="10.4.0" />
    <PackageReference Include="ModelContextProtocol" Version="1.2.0" NoWarn="NU1605;NU1608" />
    <PackageReference Include="NAudio" Version="2.2.1" />
    <PackageReference Include="RazorConsole.Core" Version="0.5.0-alpha.20260225-7c02f3c" />
    <PackageReference Include="YamlDotNet" Version="16.2.1" />
  </ItemGroup>

  <ItemGroup>
    <EmbeddedResource Include="Audio\**\*.mp3" />
  </ItemGroup>

  <ItemGroup>
    <None Include="..\..\README.md" Pack="true" PackagePath="\" />
    <None Include="MC.png" Pack="true" PackagePath="\" />
  </ItemGroup>

</Project>
